choices.text: You have a string $s$ and you may modify it by making long swaps of its letters. Two letters can be swapped if their positions differ by at least $k$. That is, you may swap the $i$-th letter with the $j$-th letter in $s$ if $|i - j| \geq k$. Is it possible to sort all the letters in $s$ increasingly, if you are allowed to swap any number of times (possibly zero)
